   <tr class=\"odd\">\n            <td>- Developer-friendly</td>\n            <td></td>\n        </tr>\n    </tbody>\n</table>","position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":1,"offset":2254},"end":{"line":45,"column":9,"offset":2985}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Before installing your SSG, you’ll need to make sure you have all the required software. Jekyll runs on the ","position":{"start":{"line":47,"column":1,"offset":2987},"end":{"line":47,"column":109,"offset":3095}}},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://www.ruby-lang.org/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Ruby stack","position":{"start":{"line":47,"column":110,"offset":3096},"end":{"line":47,"column":120,"offset":3106}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":47,"column":109,"offset":3095},"end":{"line":47,"column":149,"offset":3135}}},{"type":"text","value":", a popular choice for both desktop and web-based server applications. While developers enjoy Ruby for its strengths as a programming language, it can be a little difficult to manage from the user’s perspective. For example, on Linux you can install the core Ruby library using your distribution’s package manager, but additional modules can also come from Ruby’s own ","position":{"start":{"line":47,"column":149,"offset":3135},"end":{"line":47,"column":517,"offset":3503}}},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"gem","position":{"start":{"line":47,"column":519,"offset":3505},"end":{"line":47,"column":522,"offset":3508}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":47,"column":517,"offset":3503},"end":{"line":47,"column":524,"offset":3510}}},{"type":"text","value":" installer. If you don’t keep track of what came from where, you may run into issues if you upgrade from one source and not the other. All that said, if you’re a developer who works in Ruby already, the large ecosystem of Ruby software can lend some useful features to your chosen SSG.","position":{"start":{"line":47,"column":524,"offset":3510},"end":{"line":47,"column":809,"offset":3795}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":47,"column":1,"offset":2987},"end":{"line":47,"column":809,"offset":3795}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"img","properties":{"src":"https://d33wubrfki0l68.cloudfront.net/057395ad58854b3ebafa718e7c49035e4c2765a4/b4afc/img/uploads/compare-jekyll-hugo-ruby-go.png","alt":null},"children":[],"position":{"start":{"line":49,"column":1,"offset":3797},"end":{"line":49,"column":134,"offset":3930}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":49,"column":1,"offset":3797},"end":{"line":49,"column":134,"offset":3930}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Hugo, on the other hand, is built in the ","position":{"start":{"line":51,"column":1,"offset":3932},"end":{"line":51,"column":42,"offset":3973}}},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://golang.org/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Go programming language","position":{"start":{"line":51,"column":43,"offset":3974},"end":{"line":51,"column":66,"offset":3997}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":51,"column":42,"offset":3973},"end":{"line":51,"column":88,"offset":4019}}},{"type":"text","value":". It’s a compiled language, which means it’s very fast (compared to interpreted languages like Ruby). It’s also a relatively new language, which means the amount of additional software modules may be somewhat less compared to Ruby.","position":{"start":{"line":51,"column":88,"offset":4019},"end":{"line":51,"column":319,"offset":4250}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":51,"column":1,"offset":3932},"end":{"line":51,"column":319,"offset":4250}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Live Reload","position":{"start":{"line":53,"column":1,"offset":4252},"end"